subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
No known morphological synapomorphy (see 
Faivovich, 2005
). 

Faivovich 
et al.
(2005

; 
2006
) proposed the presence of a flat mental gland as a putative synapomorphy for this group. However, this character is widely shared among hylid species (

Brunetti 
et al.
2012

; 
2015
; 

Faivovich 
et al.
2013

) and its consideration as a synapomorphic character for this group remains dubious (
Barrio-Amorós & Brewer-Cárias 2008
).

